{
  "texts": [
    "TDA has been used in settings with limited or noisy data, such as power forecasting (Senekane et al. 2021), segmenting aerial photography (Mosinska et al. 2018) and astronomy (Murugan and Robertson 2019).",
    "In some applications, topological information may be more significant (e.g.",
    "finding anomalies or changes in topology) than statistical (e.g.",
    "pixel-wise) information.",
    "For example, in Vukicevic et al. (2017), Byrne et al. (2016) detecting holes between heart chambers was more important than inferring the thickness of septal walls."
  ]
}